Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area. There are approximately 183412 rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater "San Francisco Bay" area.

Preliminary Wrangling¶

In this step we will import necessary libraries wich will help us in our analysis and explore our data in order to make it clean and tidy ann ready for visual exploration.

there are some issues regarding quality and tidiness in this dataset:

1/ Missing values in the columns : start_station_id, start_station_name, end_station_id, end_station_name, member_birth_year, member_gender.

2/ Start and end time must be of type datetime not object

3/ Member birth year is of type float, it should be of type int

4/ start_station_id and end_station_id should be of type int not float

5/ unecessary columns must be dropped ('start_station_latitude', 'start_station_longitude', 'end_station_latitude' ,'end_station_longitude')

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 183412 rows and 16 columns in the Ford GoBike System dataset, including duration_sec, start_time, end_time, end_time, start_station_id, start_station_nam, start_station_latitude, start_station_longitude, end_station_id, end_station_name, end_station_latitude, end_station_longitude, bike_id, user_type, member_birth_year, member_gender, bike_share_for_all_trip.

I have dropped some unecessary columns and added new ones : 'Age', 'start_time_month', 'end_time_month', 'start_time_day', 'end_time_day', 'start_time_hour', 'end_time_hour', 'duration_min'. So it can be useful in the visualization section later.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features that interest me include data related to the start and end of a ride, this can be used to calculate when bikes are in high or low demand.

There is also data related to the users of the bike service including their age, gender, and whether they are a paying member or a casual user.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The start and end times, and related time-based information such as month, hour, day.. will be useful for analysis.

#function to plot countplot in matplotlib :

def countplot(dataset, x_, x_label, y_label, title, size):
    plt.figure(figsize = size)
    plot = sns.countplot(data=dataset, x=x_)
    plt.xlabel(x_label)
    plt.ylabel(y_label)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

# Customer Daily Usage vs. Subscriber Daily Usage
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))

df_user = df_copy.groupby(['start_time_day', 'user_type']).size().reset_index()

days = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']

ax = sns.pointplot(data=df_user, x='start_time_day', y=0, hue = 'user_type', scale=.7, order = days);

plt.title('Ford GoBike rides by User Type', y=1.05, fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel('days')
plt.ylabel('Number of Bike Trips');
plt.grid()

Obseravtion

Customers have a very low usage of the bike share system with a small increase on Thursdays.

Subscribers are the opposite. The rate of bike riders are very high especially on Thursdays but it drops significantly on Saturdays and Sundays.

Conclusions¶

Renting a bike from theFord GoBike System Riding should be on top of the list if you have no plans for the holidays or even on weekdays. It is not only fun but also, it is a perfect activity for unwinding and keeping your body active.

The best part is that you do not have to worry about owning a bike. With rentals, you can easily access a bike for as long as you wish and have as much fun as you want.

There are two types of clients using this system: Subscribers and Customers. Subscribers are primarily daily commuters, having short trips to and from their destination which can be estimated as work or school, who rent a bike on weekdays at 8-9am and 5-6pm.

Customers are usually occassional riders who use the system mainly on weekends or certain days such as Thursdays to explore the Bay Area probably.

Limitations for this project :¶

-Many null data points were present in the dataset, which had to be dealt with.

-Some users have 100 or more as their age, these were outliers that had to be cleaned.
